Components.Name: Round To Factor
Components.Description: Round a number to a multiplication factor.

Parameters.Name: Round Type
Parameters.Description:
Determines how the number is rounded

0 = Nearest
1 = Floor
2 = Ceiling

Parameters.Name: Rounded
Parameters.Description:
Resulting rounded number from rounding x to the multiplication factor

The decimal places of this number can only be displayed up until the amount set in Grasshopper's formatting options (File>Preferences>Display>Formatting), those settings only change how a number is displayed, they do not change the actual value of the number itself. Additionally, unecessary trailing zeros won't be displayed because of Grasshopper.

Parameters.Name: Difference
Parameters.Description: The difference between the resulting rounded number and the input number x

Parameters.Name: Multiplier R
Parameters.Description: The number of times the multiplication factor fits into the resulting rounded number

Parameters.Name: Multiplier X
Parameters.Description: The number of times the multiplication factor fits into the input number x
